body: "Why this exists: PR#565 (pm-cpja) shipped scanHistoryAuthorAttribution scanning ALL history with no window (src/sdk/author-attribution.ts). The 162 flagged events predate author discipline and can NEVER be repaired: history streams are append-only immutable proof, so rewriting authors is forbidden by design. Without a legacy/actionable split the warning is permanent noise that violates the every-warning-maps-to-an-actionable-owner invariant. Precedents: pm-2ler (dangling_dependency_references active-only gating with legacy informational count) and pm-e9zh (missing_close_reason legacy set, never hand-backfill). Remediation for NEW events is prevention only: PM_AUTHOR, global --author, or config author_default."
